Certainly! Here's how you can modify the code to create a section in the Kavo UI library:

```lua
local Library = loadstring(game:HttpGet("https://pastebin.com/raw/edJT9EGX", true))()
local Window = Library.CreateLib("Toggle Example", "DarkTheme")

local MovementSection = Window:NewSection("Movement")

local Toggle = MovementSection:NewToggle("Continuous Forward Movement", function(state)
    if state then
        RunMovement()
    else
        StopMovement()
    end
end)

local Player = game:GetService("Players").LocalPlayer
local Running = false

function RunMovement()
    if not Running then
        Running = true
        while Running do
            Player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame = Player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame + Player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame.lookVector * 1
            Player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame = Player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame + Player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame.lookVector * 1
            Player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame = Player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame + Player.Character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame.lookVector * 1
            wait(0.005)
        end
    end
end

function StopMovement()
    Running = false
end
```

In this modified code, a new section called "Movement" is created using `Window:NewSection()`. The toggle for continuous forward movement is then created inside this section using `MovementSection:NewToggle()`. The rest of the code remains the same.

You can customize the section and toggle names as per your preference. Remember to replace the Kavo UI library link (`https://pastebin.com/raw/edJT9EGX`) with the correct link, if needed.
